<h1><span id="French_Defence:_Advance_Variation">French Defence: Advance Variation</span></h1>
<p>By playing 6.a3 White eliminates any possibility of a b4 intrusion. Also White is preparing to assert himself on the queenside
via b2-b4.Furthermore, b2-b4 frees the c1 bishop from minding the b2 pawn.
</p>
<p><b>1.e4 e6 2.d4 d5 3.e5 c5 4.c3 Nc6 5.Nf3 Qb6 6.a3</b>
</p>
